						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Rājarājakēśarivarmaṉ (Rājarāja I) Year 8: 993 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records the gift of land for burning lamps as <hi rend="italic">tiruviḷakkuppuṟam</hi> by the <hi rend="italic">ūrār</hi> of Marudāḍu to the temple of Peruntirkkōyil-āḻvār for the merit of Taḍaṅgan Ayyaṉ Kalipperumān of Māgaṉūrp-pūttuṟai, who died so that the village Marudāḍu, which was in Marudāḍu-nāḍu in Veṇkuṉṟa-kōṭṭam, may not be destroyed <hi rend="italic">(aḻiyāmaiyaṉṟu).</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription suggests that both the <hi rend="italic">ūrār</hi> and <hi rend="italic">nāṭṭavar</hi> are the same local bodies.</p>						

						</summary>
